║   MODEL C: OFFSET + INTERACTION                              ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

SPECIFICATION:
  Background: μ(d,y) = population × exp(β₀ + δ·log(pop) + Σ β_year)
  Triggering: α(marks) = exp(β₀_trig + β_violence·violent + β_state·intervention)
  Kernel: g(t) = exp(-β·t)
  Intensity: λ(t) = μ(d,y) + Σ α(marks_i)·g(t-t_i)

KEY ASSUMPTION:
  → Population is EXPOSURE (multiplicative)
  → But per-capita rates can vary with population (δ coefficient)
  → Flexible model: nests both offset (δ=0) and power-law models
  → If δ < 0: larger districts have lower per-capita rates
  → If δ > 0: larger districts have higher per-capita rates

PARAMETERS (15 total):
  Background (11): β₀, δ, β_2016...β_2024
  Triggering (3): β₀_trig, β_violence, β_state
  Decay (1): β

